  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kibera Drought Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Install five 5,000 L water tanks for schools and communities, distribute 10,000 chlorine tablets for water sanitation, support 400 Community Health Workers to distribute oral re-hydration salts, distribute food supplements for pregnant women, lactating mothers, children under 5 years as well as people living with HIV/AIDS and increase access to safe water and decrease sanitation and hygiene related diseases among school children. Construct 40 door latrines in three schools, establish a Child Health Care Clinic for malnourished children,  provide Vitamin A supplements and medical outreach.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Kibera drought response focuses on providing health services to the influx of people coming to Kibera from other affected areas. This includes the installation of water tanks, distribution of water purification tablets, construction of school latrines, and the distribution of nutritional supplements for pregnant women, lactating mothers, people living with HIV/AIDS, and children under five years of age.</narrative>
  </description>
